      </section>

      <section class="card">
        <h2>What you’re inviting them to review</h2>
        <p>
          SharpeSystem is being built as a structured orientation layer: decision trees, scope notices,
          and disciplined process prompts that reduce procedural drift and improve the quality of client-provided information.
        </p>

        <div class="hr"></div>

        <h2>Why attorneys might care</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Cleaner intake:</strong> fewer scattered narratives, more structured facts.</li>
          <li><strong>Lower friction:</strong> clients stop re-litigating basics and start answering the right questions.</li>
          <li><strong>Better documentation:</strong> consistent, time-stamped records.</li>
          <li><strong>Boundary clarity:</strong> explicitly non-advice and non-directive.</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="note">
